    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Fuel System - Fuel Filter Tower,
        Bracket and Piping
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Fuel Filter Tower, Bracket and Piping</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="5">
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, do not
                        smoke or work near open flames and sparks when draining fuel.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1201203" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3292.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Fuel Filter Lever Locations</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Shutoff Lever, CLOSED Position</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Shutoff Lever, DRAIN Position</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a suitable container at the end of the fuel filter drain line to catch the
                    draining fuel. Move the fuel filter drain lever to the DRAIN position. When the fuel is done
                    draining, return the lever to the CLOSED position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201205" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9140.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Fuel Lines</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Supply to Fuel Transfer Pump Line</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Transfer Pump to Fuel Filter Line</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter to Fuel Transfer Pump Line</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Drain Line</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolt for the retaining clamp that holds three of the fuel lines together.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the hose clamps and remove all four fuel lines.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201204" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg7/EG7460.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing Hoses from the Regulating Valve</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Pressure Regulating Valve</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Supply Hoses</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two fuel supply hoses from the fuel pressure regulating valve. Cap the fittings
                    on the cylinder head.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolts that secure the fuel pressure regulating valve to the fuel filter.
                    Check for damage or corrosion.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2051211" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg7/EG7467.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Fuel Filter Tower (Model Year 1997-1998)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Tower</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Support Bracket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Tower Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Support Bracket Mounting Nuts (4)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1201207" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figf11/F1103.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Fuel Filter Tower (Model Years 1999 and Up)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Tower</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Support Bracket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Tower Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Support Bracket Mounting Nuts (3)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two mounting bolts that secure the fuel filter tower to the fuel filter
                    support bracket. Remove the fuel filter tower from the support bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If necessary, remove the mounting nuts that secure the fuel filter support bracket to
                    the cylinder head. Remove the support bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
